rule.description: All non-symbolic TrueType fonts shall have either MacRomanEncoding or WinAnsiEncoding as the value for the Encoding key in the Font dictionary or as the value for the BaseEncoding key in the dictionary that is the value of the Encoding key in the Font dictionary. In addition, all non-symbolic TrueType fonts shall not define a Differences array unless all of the glyph names in the Differences array are listed in the Adobe Glyph List and the embedded font program contains at least the Microsoft Unicode (3,1 â€“ Platform ID = 3, Encoding ID = 1) encoding in the 'cmap' table
